node.text:
We're kicking off our first est film production with a momentous Malvern Home renovation by @dohertydesignstudio from est magazine issue #35.
.
Tapping into its rich architectural past and 1980s new wave bones, @dohertydesignstudio have skilfully commandeered an epic journey to reinvent this Melbourne family home. An original 1980's design by architect Peter McIntyre. .
.
Experience the entire home via the link in profile or read the full feature in est magazine issue #35. .
.
Design @dohertydesignstudio
Building design @arialexander
Builder @north_building_group 
Styling @heathernetteking 
Florals and assitant styling @rachelpolivkastylist 
Art consultant @gb.art.consulting 
Landscape design @benscott_design 
Videography @richardlipp.studio
Words @meganmayrawson
Art @tompolo @liamsnootle @anyapesce @oocaleb @davidjamesgriggs @christianthompsonartist #leekyoung-hwa 
Furniture & Objects @domoaustralia @lightlydesign @loomtowels @fenton_and_fenton @abode_living @moderntimesau @ajarfurniture @lamarzoccohomeau

node.text:
Great land. Great architecture. Great living. In an est exclusive, we feature three unique films by Rob Mills Architecture & Interiors (RMA). Australian-based RMA’s latest project, a ground-breaking residence in Byron Bay incorporates Mill’s signature use of drama, curves, lines, light and a reflection of the qualities of the land.
.
View all three films via link in profile.
.
Videography @collider__
Creative Direction | Design @robmillsarchitects

node.text:
INTERVIEW | Directors of Caprini & Pellerin
​.
"French architecture is a bit like French gastronomy; very rich and diverse! There are many different styles. We are very much in awe of French craftsmanship and ancient know-how. We are fascinated by old stone constructions and how they were built back in the day, particularly castles, palaces, farmhouses, and convents."
​– Jerry Pellerin
​.
​Read more from French architects Jerry Pellerin and Kevin Caprini in our interview – link in profile.
​.
​Design @caprinipellerinarchitectes 
​Styling  @sarahdebeaumont
​Photography @alexisarmanet
​.
​https://www.estliving.com/interview-caprini-pellerin-directors-kevin-caprini-jerry-pellerin/

node.text:
INTERIORS | Marin County House
​.
​Together with @marmolradziner, @chromasf revive a 70s home in San Francisco’s Marin County through an eclectic assemblage of decadent vintage textures, shapes and colours. 
.
The collaboration reveals their intent to design a family home that feels far from the fact, through each eye-catching and iconic piece, the carefully selected material palette and vistas that appreciate the surrounding greenery, 
​.
​Architecture @marmolradziner
​Design @chromasf
​Photography @stephenkentjohnson
​.
​https://www.estliving.com/

SPACES | Above Board Living
​.
@luigirosselliarchitects designed 'Above Board Living' for a client passionate about design and their close proximity to Bronte Beach. 
​.
The rammed earth home takes its name from how the home is structured, where the main living areas and kitchen are all located on the upper level to make the most of the sea breeze and views below. 
​.
​See more of this project inside 'Spaces' on estliving.com – link in profile. 
​.
​Design @luigirosselliarchitects 
​Build @groundup_build
​Landscaping @podlandscaping
Photography @prueruscoe 
​.
​https://www.estliving.com/spaces/kitchen-above-board-living-kitchen-luigi-rosselli-architects/

.

node.text:
DINING OF THE MONTH | Seaside Retreat
​.
The Seaside Retreat dining nook by @stef_claes was our most popular dining space in July.
.
A show of craftsmanship, the dining nook extends the potential for guests, nodding to the ‘50s with the Tulip dining table by Eero Saarinen, 26A pendant by Isamu Noguchi and the Medea Chairs by Vitterio Nobile for Fratelli Tagliabue that feel right at home with their curved plywood shell.
.
See this dining space and more dining inspiration on www.estliving.com - link in profile. 
.
Design @stef_claes
​Photography @cb
​.
​https://www.estliving.com/spaces/dining-seaside-retreat-dining-stef-claes/

AT HOME WITH | Athena Calderone
​.
​Athena Calderone's Amagansett Home explores her passion for finding timeworn design pieces that tell their own story.
​.
An amalgamation of styles and time periods, the mid-century renovation sees a personal curation of mostly vintage pieces as part of a textural scheme that blends rattan, boucle, sisal, brass and walnut.
​.
​Design @eyeswoon 
​Photography @nicole_franzen 
​.
​https://www.estliving.com/

node.text:
KITCHEN COVET | Concrete in the Kitchen
​.
​Concrete has left its strict worksite ties behind to make a case in kitchen design. Be it a benchtop, backsplash or monolithic kitchen island, architects and designers worldwide lean on the natural composite material for a lasting impression in the kitchen. 
​.
Together with @fisherpaykel, we explore how the porous material, and its variations in colour and finish, take form in 10 different kitchen projects.
​.
​Read more about concrete in the kitchen on estliving.com – link in profile. 
​.
​Design @alexander_andco, @marplusask, @robkennonarchitects, @jhinteriordesign, @traviswalton_architecture, @madeleineblanchfieldarchitects, @auhaus, @wolveridge,  @breathearchitecture & @lande.archi
​Photography @smartanson, @piet.albert.goethals, @derekswalwell, @aaronleitz, @elisawatson_photography, @davekulesza & @shannonmcgrath7
​.
​https://www.estliving.com/kitchen-covet-concrete-kitchen/

BEDROOM OF THE MONTH | The Audo
​.
The Audo bedroom was our most popular in July, part of Copenhagen's design destination, The Audo hybrid space by @normarchitects.
​.
​The Audo Residence comprises of 10 unique guest rooms, varying in size and each designed with a unique colour story. As an extension of the experiential showroom, no two suites are the same and reminiscent of a collector’s home.
​.
Be inspired by our bedroom of the month via our link in profile. 
​.
​Design and photography @normarchitects
​.
​https://www.estliving.com/spaces/bedroom-the-audo-norm-architects/

​.
​@studio10design were asked to redesign the interiors of a home Shenzhen, China with a distinctly Italian influence. 
​.

​.
​Design @studio10design
​Photography Chao Zhang
​.
​https://www.estliving.com/
